1
00:00:03,903 --> 00:00:07,202
<i>##[Chorus Singing]</i>

2
00:00:10,143 --> 00:00:12,202
<i>[Bell Ringing]</i>

3
00:00:12,312 --> 00:00:14,212
[Tires Screeching]

4
00:00:15,448 --> 00:00:17,541
D'oh!
[Screams]

5
00:00:22,522 --> 00:00:24,319
Ooh.

6
00:00:34,768 --> 00:00:37,737
[Grunting]

7
00:00:37,837 --> 00:00:41,204
Stupid heater!
Don't make me come in there.

8
00:00:41,307 --> 00:00:44,834
Why do you always wait until
Christmas Eve to do your shopping?

9
00:00:44,944 --> 00:00:47,139
The crowds are just beastly.

10
00:00:47,247 --> 00:00:50,182
You know me, Marge.
I crave the hustle and bustle.

11
00:00:52,452 --> 00:00:56,354
[Grunting]

12
00:01:04,998 --> 00:01:06,829
[Grunts]

13
00:01:06,933 --> 00:01:10,596
- <i>[Chattering]</i>
- Homer, look at this mob.

14
00:01:10,703 --> 00:01:13,069
The good toys
are probably all gone.

15
00:01:13,173 --> 00:01:17,371
[Chuckles] Oh, Santa's got
a little trick up his sleeve.

16
00:01:17,477 --> 00:01:22,676
Attention shoppers, Register 9 is now
open for your shopping convenience.

17
00:01:22,782 --> 00:01:25,307
Sorry, these are for display only.
This has been recalled.

18
00:01:25,418 --> 00:01:27,318
Ooh, Bart would like this.
We're out of these.

19
00:01:27,420 --> 00:01:30,184
- Out? But I just-
- Register 9 is now closed.

20
00:01:33,059 --> 00:01:35,926
[Giggles]

21
00:01:40,867 --> 00:01:43,768
<i>Hey, kids.</i>
<i>I made your favorite cookies.</i>

22
00:01:43,870 --> 00:01:47,499
Christmas trees for the girls
and bloody spearheads for Bart.

23
00:01:47,607 --> 00:01:50,303
Aw, thanks, Mom.

24
00:01:50,410 --> 00:01:52,935
[Groaning]

25
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:57,379
This year's tree is just perfect.

26
00:01:57,484 --> 00:01:59,611
That old aluminium one was so fake.

27
00:01:59,719 --> 00:02:01,619
I couldn't agree more.

28
00:02:01,721 --> 00:02:05,953
From now on,
it's plastic all the way.

29
00:02:06,059 --> 00:02:07,959
- <i>[Footsteps]</i>
- <i>[Bells Jingling]</i>

30
00:02:08,061 --> 00:02:11,326
- Bart, did you hear that?
- Could it be?

31
00:02:14,534 --> 00:02:18,061
- [Screaming]
- Whoa!

32
00:02:18,171 --> 00:02:20,071
[Laughing]

33
00:02:20,173 --> 00:02:22,073
[Whimpering]

34
00:02:25,512 --> 00:02:27,309
Come on, kids.
Let's try the lights.

35
00:02:30,450 --> 00:02:32,748
<i>[Electrical Crackling]</i>

36
00:02:36,289 --> 00:02:38,883
It's "craptacular."

37
00:02:43,763 --> 00:02:45,663
[Bleating]

38
00:02:46,699 --> 00:02:48,599
Hocus-pocus.

39
00:02:48,701 --> 00:02:50,828
Mucous "pukeous."

40
00:02:50,937 --> 00:02:52,837
My powers of
deduction tell me...

41
00:02:52,939 --> 00:02:58,275
you're getting a handmade
sweater, possibly yellow.

42
00:02:58,378 --> 00:03:00,278
Mom, make him stop!

43
00:03:00,380 --> 00:03:02,280
Bart, put down
that yellow sweater.

44
00:03:02,382 --> 00:03:06,318
Nobody's going near their presents
until 7:00 tomorrow morning.

45
00:03:06,419 --> 00:03:10,753
- [All Groaning]
- <i>7:00 a.m., no earlier.</i>

46
00:03:10,857 --> 00:03:14,816
And you can't set your alarm clocks,
'cause I've got 'em.

47
00:03:14,928 --> 00:03:19,058
- For once, we're gonna
celebrate Christmas as a family.
- <i>[Knocking]</i>

48
00:03:19,165 --> 00:03:22,794
Hello? Anybody home?

49
00:03:30,743 --> 00:03:33,712
Twelve glasses of water.
That will wake me up nice and early.

50
00:03:33,813 --> 00:03:36,577
And I'll have a big head start
on opening presents.

51
00:03:36,683 --> 00:03:39,208
- Pure genius.
- You didn't invent that, Bart.

52
00:03:39,319 --> 00:03:43,050
The Indians used to drink water
to wake up early for their attacks.

53
00:03:43,156 --> 00:03:46,683
[Groans]
It's always about the Indians, isn't it, Lise?

54
00:03:46,793 --> 00:03:50,422
Dear Santa, if you bring me
lots of good stuff...

55
00:03:50,530 --> 00:03:52,998
I promise not to do anything bad...

56
00:03:53,099 --> 00:03:55,329
between now
and when I wake up, amen.

57
00:03:55,435 --> 00:03:58,996
Ow! I'll kill you.

58
00:04:00,106 --> 00:04:03,940
<i>[Water Dripping]</i>

59
00:04:07,380 --> 00:04:10,042
<i>[Dripping Continues]</i>

60
00:04:12,085 --> 00:04:14,679
[Screaming]

61
00:04:23,529 --> 00:04:26,259
<i>[Thunderclap]</i>

62
00:04:30,103 --> 00:04:32,571
- There you go.
- Get him up there.

63
00:04:32,672 --> 00:04:36,130
<i>[Crowd Cheering]</i>

64
00:04:37,176 --> 00:04:40,304
Go! Go! Go! We're number one!

65
00:04:40,413 --> 00:04:42,711
- Give me a "P"!
- "P"!

66
00:04:42,815 --> 00:04:46,376
Go! Go! Go!
"P"! "P"! "P"!

67
00:04:49,789 --> 00:04:52,553
[Chuckles]
Worked like a charm.

68
00:04:52,659 --> 00:04:54,559
[Groaning]

69
00:04:54,661 --> 00:04:57,824
<i>[Toilet Flushing]</i>

70
00:04:57,930 --> 00:05:02,230
[Sighs]
How sweet it is.

71
00:05:05,004 --> 00:05:07,564
Hmm.

72
00:05:07,674 --> 00:05:10,302
[Laughing]

73
00:05:15,014 --> 00:05:19,314
Oh, Aunt Selma.
Always good for a fin.

74
00:05:19,419 --> 00:05:21,649
Whoa, here we go.

75
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:29,060
[Gasps]
The Inferno Buster 3000!

76
00:05:29,162 --> 00:05:33,861
Oh, I knew Santa wouldn't
have time to check that list twice.

77
00:05:35,902 --> 00:05:37,767
Oh, yeah.

78
00:05:40,540 --> 00:05:43,008
- Cool.
- <i>[Siren Wailing]</i>

79
00:05:45,311 --> 00:05:47,836
Uh-oh.

80
00:05:49,682 --> 00:05:51,707
Eek!

81
00:05:51,818 --> 00:05:54,685
[Screaming]

82
00:06:02,995 --> 00:06:05,555
Who designed this house?

83
00:06:15,475 --> 00:06:17,773
[Bleating]

84
00:06:20,113 --> 00:06:23,913
Homer. Homer,
I think I heard a noise.

85
00:06:24,016 --> 00:06:27,247
[Bleating]

86
00:06:29,088 --> 00:06:31,056
[Breathing]

87
00:06:33,059 --> 00:06:35,118
Knock it off.

88
00:06:45,371 --> 00:06:48,204
Snow covers all.
Pure, white snow.

89
00:06:57,016 --> 00:07:01,112
[Gasps, Gulps]
I gotta get back to bed.

90
00:07:01,220 --> 00:07:04,383
- <i>[Marge Gasps] What happened?</i>
- [Gasps]

91
00:07:04,490 --> 00:07:08,324
[Stammering]
Where's Christmas?

92
00:07:08,428 --> 00:07:11,591
Lisa, where's Christmas?

93
00:07:11,697 --> 00:07:13,927
Bart, what were you
doing outside?

94
00:07:15,802 --> 00:07:17,793
I don't know how
to tell you this, but...

95
00:07:17,904 --> 00:07:20,498
I came down a little early, and...

96
00:07:20,606 --> 00:07:25,475
<i>uh, well, uh...</i>

97
00:07:25,578 --> 00:07:29,742
I saw a burglar
and he was- he took-

98
00:07:29,849 --> 00:07:33,376
[Sobbing]
he got all our stuff.

99
00:07:33,486 --> 00:07:37,047
Including the tree.
[Sobbing]

100
00:07:37,156 --> 00:07:41,024
- We were robbed?
- [Sobbing] Uh-huh, uh-huh, uh-huh.

101
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:42,651
- [Gasping]
- How could somebody-

102
00:07:42,762 --> 00:07:46,289
I know!
[Sobbing]

103
00:07:46,399 --> 00:07:52,201
[Sobbing]
Can... we... skip... church?

104
00:07:57,443 --> 00:08:01,174
Now, uh, what did this
Christmas thief look like?

105
00:08:01,280 --> 00:08:05,011
Well, he had a glass eye,
a wooden leg...

106
00:08:05,117 --> 00:08:09,110
- a big scar on his cheek.
- Anything unusual?

107
00:08:09,222 --> 00:08:12,851
Hooks for hands, uh- Oh, he was
wearing a striped convict's shirt.

108
00:08:12,959 --> 00:08:15,325
He was carrying a big sack
with a dollar sign on it.

109
00:08:15,428 --> 00:08:17,521
[Scoffs]
Classic burglar.

110
00:08:17,630 --> 00:08:20,326
Aw, cheer up.
We'll catch this guy.

111
00:08:20,433 --> 00:08:25,461
- Uh, chief-
- What? You can't rule it out.

112
00:08:25,571 --> 00:08:28,335
- <i>[Door Shuts]</i>
- Well, there's no easy way to say it, kid.

113
00:08:28,441 --> 00:08:30,341
God hates us.

114
00:08:30,443 --> 00:08:33,037
Hey, since when is Christmas
just about the presents?

115
00:08:33,145 --> 00:08:37,707
Arert we forgetting the true meaning
of this day? The birth of Santa.

116
00:08:37,817 --> 00:08:39,717
Bart's absolutely right.

117
00:08:39,819 --> 00:08:43,277
This is the one day that
shouldn't be about material things.

118
00:08:43,389 --> 00:08:46,381
Hey, why don't we walk over to
Grampa's and cheer up the old folks?

119
00:08:46,492 --> 00:08:50,223
- That will make us feel better.
- Oh, okay.

120
00:08:50,329 --> 00:08:53,298
But they'll have to be pretty damn
miserable to make me happy.

121
00:08:57,436 --> 00:08:59,996
<i>##[Christmas Carols On Stereo]</i>

122
00:09:00,106 --> 00:09:03,098
Looks like the Flanders
are having a nice Christmas.

123
00:09:03,209 --> 00:09:05,109
Oh, yeah?
We'll show 'em.

124
00:09:05,211 --> 00:09:08,180
Come on, kids. Pretend
we got new cross-country skis.

125
00:09:18,124 --> 00:09:20,592
[Honking]

126
00:09:20,693 --> 00:09:23,457
Merry Christmas, Simpsons!
[Laughing]

127
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:30,164
That's not as fun as it looks.

128
00:09:30,269 --> 00:09:32,669
Nothing could be as fun as that looks.

129
00:09:32,772 --> 00:09:35,673
<i>Hey, look what I got, Bart!</i>
<i>A Tickle Me Krusty!</i>

130
00:09:35,775 --> 00:09:38,801
- [Goofy Laugh] Hey, kid,
get your finger out of there.
- [Laughing]

131
00:09:38,911 --> 00:09:40,538
- Ow!
- <i>[Marge] Homer!</i>

132
00:09:41,981 --> 00:09:43,972
<i>##[Christmas Rop On Stereo]</i>

133
00:09:44,083 --> 00:09:47,280
Lisa, you promised they'd be miserable.
What the hell's going on?

134
00:09:47,386 --> 00:09:53,291
Oh, the pharmaceutical man come by
and he shot us full of Christmas cheer.

135
00:09:53,392 --> 00:09:55,360
[Laughing]

136
00:09:55,461 --> 00:09:57,986
I can't feel nothing
below my chin.

137
00:09:58,097 --> 00:10:00,531
<i>##[Continues]</i>

138
00:10:01,934 --> 00:10:03,902
[Squeaking]

139
00:10:05,304 --> 00:10:08,000
Ah, sounds like you're having
a rough Christmas, Homer.

140
00:10:08,107 --> 00:10:10,302
You know what I blame this
on the breakdown of?

141
00:10:10,409 --> 00:10:12,877
- Society.
- Yeah.

142
00:10:12,979 --> 00:10:16,312
You're right, Moe.
You're always Moe.

143
00:10:16,415 --> 00:10:19,043
Homer, look.
Your house is on TV.

144
00:10:19,151 --> 00:10:21,779
You take that back, Barney.

145
00:10:21,887 --> 00:10:24,856
- No, he's right, Homer.
- Stay out of this, old man.

146
00:10:24,957 --> 00:10:29,018
<i>Dateline, Kent Brockman. I'm here at</i>
<i>the scene of the Christmas burglary...</i>

147
00:10:29,128 --> 00:10:31,096
where a creature
was stirring last night...

148
00:10:31,197 --> 00:10:34,826
and what he was stirring
was up trouble.

149
00:10:34,934 --> 00:10:36,959
Is your husband
or lover here, ma'am?

150
00:10:37,069 --> 00:10:40,232
No, my husband is...
at church.

151
00:10:40,339 --> 00:10:44,036
Aw, that's my girl.
I love you, Marjorie.

152
00:10:44,143 --> 00:10:47,135
- Yeah, she's quite a gal.
- You shut up.

153
00:10:47,246 --> 00:10:51,774
So when you realized Christmas
was ruined, how did you feel?

154
00:10:51,884 --> 00:10:53,784
How do you think I felt?

155
00:10:53,886 --> 00:10:56,013
Absolutely devastated.

156
00:10:56,122 --> 00:10:58,420
"Absolutely devastated."

157
00:10:58,524 --> 00:11:00,822
The words of
a heartbroken mother.

158
00:11:00,926 --> 00:11:03,656
For there will be no
fire truck for little Bart...

159
00:11:03,763 --> 00:11:05,856
no sweater for little Lisa...

160
00:11:05,965 --> 00:11:08,229
no Cajun sausage for little Homer.

161
00:11:08,334 --> 00:11:12,236
- [Wails]
- So while you're home today...

162
00:11:12,338 --> 00:11:15,330
eating your sweet,
sweet holiday turkey...

163
00:11:15,441 --> 00:11:19,434
I hope you'll all choke
just a little bit.

164
00:11:22,515 --> 00:11:24,745
Lousy doormat.

165
00:11:26,285 --> 00:11:29,743
Homer, you won't believe
what's happened. It's a miracle.

166
00:11:29,855 --> 00:11:33,291
Aw, Marge, I don't wanna hear
any more about that silver polish.

167
00:11:34,694 --> 00:11:37,595
- Surprise!
- [Cheering]

168
00:11:37,697 --> 00:11:40,632
- ## [Christmas Carol]
- People saw our story on the news...

169
00:11:40,733 --> 00:11:43,099
and they've opened
their hearts to us.

170
00:11:43,202 --> 00:11:46,035
Yar, we just gave
what we could.

171
00:11:46,138 --> 00:11:48,038
Does anyone have
change for a button?

172
00:11:48,140 --> 00:11:51,109
- Wow, this really restores your faith in-
- <i>##[Continues]</i>

173
00:11:51,210 --> 00:11:54,577
Lisa! Do you have to practice
that stupid song now?

174
00:11:54,680 --> 00:11:58,810
- Sorry, Daddy.
- Hey, heard some no-goodnik stole your tree.

175
00:11:58,918 --> 00:12:02,046
Well, we got a 30-footer,
so you can have the top of ours.

176
00:12:02,154 --> 00:12:04,122
Thanks, Ted.

177
00:12:06,525 --> 00:12:08,618
Bart, this is Patches.

178
00:12:08,728 --> 00:12:10,958
- And what was your name?
- Poor Violet.

179
00:12:11,063 --> 00:12:13,361
Oh, I don't like
where this is going.

180
00:12:13,466 --> 00:12:18,529
Your story made everyone
at the orphanage so sad.

181
00:12:18,637 --> 00:12:23,438
- We want you to have this dollar we were saving.
- Please, I don't deserve this.

182
00:12:23,542 --> 00:12:25,442
Hey, listen up, everybody.

183
00:12:25,544 --> 00:12:27,671
The Simpsons are
the best friends I ever had.

184
00:12:27,780 --> 00:12:30,374
So I'm giving them
the tip jar from the bar.

185
00:12:30,483 --> 00:12:32,781
[Cheering, Laughing]

186
00:12:35,621 --> 00:12:39,352
My goodness,
there is over $15,000 here.

187
00:12:39,458 --> 00:12:43,258
15,000 Missoulians?
Holy "schlamola"!

188
00:12:43,362 --> 00:12:45,262
What are you gonna do
with all that "kablingy"?

189
00:12:45,364 --> 00:12:47,264
Well, if you mean the money...

190
00:12:47,366 --> 00:12:49,926
I suppose we'll just replace
the items the burglar took-

191
00:12:50,035 --> 00:12:52,162
Boring!
Spend it on something fun.

192
00:12:52,271 --> 00:12:56,139
- Go wild! Ha! Right, Seymour?
- Yes, something wild.

193
00:12:56,242 --> 00:12:58,233
- Yeah, enjoy, huh?
- Get something fun.

194
00:12:58,344 --> 00:13:02,644
- Something stupid.
- You only live once.
- Speak for yourself.

195
00:13:02,748 --> 00:13:06,411
Marge, kids, let's go
buy some happiness.

196
00:13:06,519 --> 00:13:09,044
[Cheering]

197
00:13:10,156 --> 00:13:12,750
God bless you, Bart Simpson.

198
00:13:12,858 --> 00:13:16,385
I'd kiss you, but Doctor says I'm sick.

199
00:13:16,495 --> 00:13:18,725
[Coughs]

200
00:13:22,468 --> 00:13:25,369
Is this car $15,000?

201
00:13:25,471 --> 00:13:28,406
Yeah, it is now.
And because of your loss, folks...

202
00:13:28,507 --> 00:13:34,036
I'll throw in the undercoating for...
200- No, 490 bucks.

203
00:13:34,146 --> 00:13:36,671
What a deal.
I'd be a sucker not to get it.

204
00:13:36,782 --> 00:13:38,682
I don't know about this, Dad.

205
00:13:38,784 --> 00:13:41,685
Shouldrt we give the money
to charity or some- Ow!

206
00:13:41,787 --> 00:13:43,982
Oh, I'm sorry.
I jabbed you with my pen.

207
00:13:44,089 --> 00:13:46,250
- Ow! You're still doing it.
- Yeah, I know.

208
00:13:46,358 --> 00:13:49,589
## [Singing Christmas Carol]

209
00:13:52,765 --> 00:13:57,998
## [Continues]

210
00:13:58,103 --> 00:14:00,196
Oh, will this
Christmas never end?

211
00:14:01,307 --> 00:14:04,174
[Honking Horn]

212
00:14:04,276 --> 00:14:07,507
Out of my way, snow poke.

213
00:14:07,613 --> 00:14:10,741
- Slow down, Homer.
- Don't worry, honey.

214
00:14:10,850 --> 00:14:13,819
I know exactly what I'm-
Whoopsie.

215
00:14:13,919 --> 00:14:15,910
Tap the brakes.
Tap the brakes.

216
00:14:16,021 --> 00:14:17,921
- Turn into the skid.
- No, away from the skid.

217
00:14:18,023 --> 00:14:19,923
- Hit the brakes!
- Floor it!

218
00:14:20,025 --> 00:14:22,255
- Go with it!
- Shut up. One at a time.

219
00:14:22,361 --> 00:14:24,693
- Lisa?
- Bail out!

220
00:14:24,797 --> 00:14:26,958
[All Screaming]

221
00:14:30,836 --> 00:14:33,202
Oh, that was close.

222
00:14:33,305 --> 00:14:35,933
<i>[Cracking]</i>

223
00:14:37,343 --> 00:14:39,937
<i>[Explosion]</i>

224
00:14:41,347 --> 00:14:43,941
- Oh, I knew this would happen.
- Well...

225
00:14:44,049 --> 00:14:47,348
at least the burglar's
having a merry Christmas.

226
00:14:52,258 --> 00:14:54,726
- <i>Bart. You're up early.</i>
- I couldn't sleep.

227
00:14:54,827 --> 00:14:56,692
What's wrong?

228
00:14:56,795 --> 00:15:01,164
[Sighs]
There was no burglar.

229
00:15:01,267 --> 00:15:03,497
- No burglar?
- What does he mean, no burglar?

230
00:15:03,602 --> 00:15:06,070
I accidentally burned up the tree...

231
00:15:06,171 --> 00:15:08,264
and the presents.

232
00:15:08,374 --> 00:15:10,274
I'm really sorry.

233
00:15:11,877 --> 00:15:15,176
- You little-
- <i>[Homer] Lisa, no!</i>

234
00:15:15,281 --> 00:15:20,378
- Your hands are too weak.
- [Gagging]

235
00:15:20,486 --> 00:15:23,387
- Stop that.
- I'm gonna kill him.
- No, I'm killing him first.

236
00:15:23,489 --> 00:15:26,185
- [All Shouting]
- <i>[Doorbell Rings]</i>

237
